Auth Flow
1. POST /api/auth/register
   → validate email + password policy
   → bcrypt hash (cost 10)
   → send verification email
   → return { message: "Verification email sent" }

2. GET /api/auth/verify-email?token=xxx
   → validate token (24h expiry)
   → set isEmailVerified = true

3. POST /api/auth/login
   → check isEmailVerified
   → check is2faEnabled → if true, return temp token
   → issue access + refresh tokens
   → store tokenHash in DB

4. POST /api/auth/refresh
   → validate refresh token hash
   → rotate: revoke old, issue new
   → return new access + refresh tokens

5. POST /api/auth/logout
   → set revokedAt on refresh token
   → clear cookies

6. POST /api/auth/2fa/setup
   → generate TOTP secret
   → return QR code URL + backup codes

7. POST /api/auth/2fa/challenge
   → verify TOTP (±30s drift)
   → issue final tokens


