OWASP Top-10 Checklist
✅ A01 Broken Access Control
   → RBAC on every endpoint
   → Tenant isolation middleware
   → org_id on every DB query

✅ A02 Cryptographic Failures
   → bcrypt (cost 10) for passwords
   → SHA-256 for token storage
   → AES-256 for sensitive fields
   → TLS 1.2/1.3 enforced

✅ A03 Injection
   → Prisma parameterized queries (no raw SQL)
   → class-validator on all DTOs
   → whitelist: true on ValidationPipe

✅ A04 Insecure Design
   → Deny-by-default permissions
   → Maker-checker for high-value operations
   → Idempotency keys prevent double-submit

✅ A05 Security Misconfiguration
   → Helmet security headers
   → CORS whitelist only
   → Env validation at startup
   → No secrets in logs

✅ A06 Vulnerable Components
   → npm audit in CI/CD
   → Dependency scan results stored in DB
   → Automated alerts on critical CVEs

✅ A07 Auth Failures
   → Rate limiting on auth endpoints
   → Account lockout after failed attempts
   → JWT short expiry (15m)
   → Refresh token rotation

✅ A08 Software Integrity
   → Hash chain on critical records
   → Immutable audit logs
   → DB triggers prevent audit tampering

✅ A09 Logging Failures
   → All auth events logged
   → All permission denials logged
   → Correlation IDs for tracing
   → Secrets masked in logs

✅ A10 SSRF
